<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC REVIEW; ROGERS' FANS ENJOY PREDICTABLE CONCERT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON HECKMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Maybe Kenny Rogers needs a new writer -- or at least some new shtick. 
</P>
<P>
 The opening-night performance of Rogers' second annual five-night run at the 
Cerritos Center for the Performing Arts on Wednesday was a near carbon copy of 
the show he brought to the same venue last February -- a show he probably could 
do in his sleep. 
</P>
<P>
