<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAYOR GUILTY OF FRAUD, REMOVED FROM OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Talladega's three-term mayor has been convicted of fraud and thrown out of 
office for cashing $5,000 in city checks that were made out to a phony tree 
surgeon. 
</P>
<P>
 Federal jurors deliberated about 11 hours over three days before convicting 
Larry Barton on Wednesday of one count of fraud and 26 counts of money 
laundering. 
</P>
<P>
 Under state law, Barton was automatically removed from office. He faces up to 
56 months in prison when he is sentenced April 22. He was allowed to remain 
free on bond pending appeal. 
</P>
