<P>
TEEN AUTHOR TESTIFIES ON BOSNIA BEFORE PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Children in Sarajevo don't see themselves as Serbs or Croats or Muslims, 
13-year-old Zlata Filipovic told U.S. lawmakers Thursday."We just knew that the 
war came, that any moment we can be killed." 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, whose diary is being published worldwide, said all she wants is to 
go to school, maybe attend a university, get married and lead "just a normal 
life." 
</P>
