<HEADLINE>
<P>
HENRY CISNEROS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * In recent weeks, there have been numerous articles and public views on "how 
things should have been handled" regarding the response to emergency housing 
needs for quake victims. Despite negative reports of FEMA's handling of the 
situation, with all fairness we should applaud HUD Secretary Henry Cisneros for 
his personal, pro-active role and commitment in expediting our quake-damaged 
revitalization.Looking at past administrations' response in the wake of 
Hurricane Andrew and other disasters, one can only be impressed by what 
Cisneros has accomplished. 
</P>
<P>
 In just one year in office, Cisneros and HUD have had to deal with several 
natural disasters. Due to Cisneros' leadership, HUD has responded swiftly to 
meet victims' needs. Cisneros' actions deserve individual recognition, and 
should not simply be a credit on the President's approval rating. 
</P>
<P>
 We hope President Clinton acknowledges the asset that Cisneros has been, and 
will compliment him for his fruitful and constructive efforts on our behalf. 
</P>
<P>
