<P>
 First-Time Jobless Claims Up: The Labor Department reported an increase of 
32,000 in the number of Americans seeking unemployment benefits for the first 
time.The figure reversed much of the previous week's decline. The department 
said a seasonally adjusted 346,000 initial claims were filed during the week 
ended March 5. Analysts said they had expected the rise, since the previous 
week was shortened by a holiday. The increase reflected severe winter weather 
in the Northeast and Midwest, and probably lingering effects of January's 
earthquakes in Southern California. 
