ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; 2 VACANT BUILDINGS TO HOUSE BUSINESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two vacant business buildings on Ball Road will soon be rehabilitated and 
opened as an auto repair shop and convenience store. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council last week gave the owners permission to begin rehabilitating 
the two buildings, which are next to one another. 
</P>
<P>
 The new businesses are expected to open within months. The store, M & M 
Market, will be open from 7 a.m. to midnight. It will sell a variety of food 
and beverages. Alcoholic beverages, however, will not be sold there. 
</P>
<P>
 The auto shop, M & M Auto Repair, will offer engine tuneups, oil changes, smog 
testing and brake repairs. 
</P>
<P>
 City officials said that by allowing the businesses to open, the abandoned, 
vacant buildings would get cleaned up and provide another place where city 
residents could service their cars or shop for food. The new businesses will 
also provide sales tax revenue for the city. MIMI KO 
