<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; SCHOOL BOARD VOTES 4-1 FOR 4% FEE HIKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westminster School District has approved a 4% increase in residential, 
commercial and industrial development fees. 
</P>
<P>
 The board approved the increase on a 4-1 vote without comment at its regular 
meeting last week.Trustees Sheryl Neugebauer, Ron Morgan, Kathy Stirling 
Iverson and Nancy Blumenthal voted in favor of the increase. Margie Rice 
opposed it. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the new schedule, designed to adjust for inflation, residential 
development fees will increase from $1.65 to $1.72 per square foot. Fees for 
commercial and industrial development will increase from 27 cents to 28 cents, 
said George Acton, director of financial services. 
</P>
<P>
 Districts charge the fees to help provide classrooms and other school 
facilities for the students whose families move into the developed areas. 
</P>
<P>
 The district receives 61% of those charges. The rest goes to the Huntington 
Beach Union School District. Last year, Westminster School District collected 
about $47,000 in developer fees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
