ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; LOTTERY TO CHOOSE LOW-RENT TENANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An apartment complex for low-income senior citizens will hold a lottery 
Saturday for prospective residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The lottery at Villa Anaheim, 280 E. Lincoln Blvd., will determine who will 
move in to the lowest-rent units. 
</P>
<P>
 To be eligible for the 9 a.m. lottery, a one-person household's annual gross 
income cannot exceed $5,650 and a two-person household's gross income cannot be 
more than $6,356. 
</P>
<P>
 The 135-unit, gated community provides seniors with very low income the 
opportunity to live in affordable one- and two-bedroom apartments. 
</P>
<P>
 The development includes a pool, spa, sun deck and a 3,700-square-foot 
clubhouse with an activity area, bingo and television center, arts and crafts 
room, kitchen, retreat area and library. 
</P>
<P>
 Operated by American Retirement Villas of Costa Mesa, the development was 
created with the participation of the California Housing Finance Agency, the 
Century Freeway Housing Program, the city of Anaheim and the Federal Tax Credit 
Program. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information call (714) 751-7400. 
</P>
</TEXT>
