UCI SPANISH DEPT. NAMES NEW CHAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Juan Bruce-Novoa, professor of Spanish, has been appointed chairman of the 
department of Spanish and Portuguese at UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Bruce-Novoa, who joined the UCI faculty in 1989, is the author of several 
books and more than 100 scholarly papers regarding Mexican and Latino 
literatures and cultures. His books include "Chicano Poetry: A Response to 
Chaos," and "Chicano Authors, Inquiry by Interview." 
</P>
