<P>
BRIEFCASE: TRAVEL AND TOURISM; AIRPORT NOT SURE WHERE IT WILL PUT SOUTHWEST 
AIRLINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Now that Southwest Airlines plans to operate 17 flights, including the two it 
picks up from Morris Air Service, at John Wayne Airport, where will you find 
its counter? 
</P>
<P>
 Airport officials aren't sure yet.Spokeswoman Courtney Wiercioch said she 
thinks the Southwest counter will probably be in the south end of the terminal. 
That would be a change for Morris Air passengers, who are used to checking in 
for their flights at a counter in the north end that Morris subleases from 
American Airlines. 
</P>
<P>
 American will probably be glad to see Morris go. Southwest's expected low 
fares may so badly undercut American on its eight daily flights to San Jose 
that American may pull off the route. 
</P>
<P>
 Southwest says it expects to begin service May 26. 
