<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: COMMUNITY COLLEGE DISTRICT REORGANIZING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Community College District announced Thursday that it is 
reorganizing its administration -- effectively cutting three positions -- in an 
effort to cut costs. 
</P>
<P>
 Spokesman Fausto Capobianco said that within the district's Educational 
Services Division, the positions of director of student services and director 
of instructional programs have been consolidated into a new position called 
senior director of educational services. 
</P>
<P>
 That post has been filled by Victoria Munoz Richart, former vice president of 
academic affairs at Mission College in Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
 The directorship of student services has been vacant for several months, 
Capobianco said. 
</P>
<P>
 An administrative analyst position in the office of the president of Mission 
College has also been cut and the person who held the position reassigned. 
</P>
<P>
 Also slashed was the position of executive assistant to the district 
chancellor. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosalind Goddard, who vacates that position, will become acting associate dean 
of administrative services at Southwest College in Los Angeles. KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</TEXT>
