CAMPBELL QUITS AS CONCORDIA BASKETBALL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Concordia women's basketball Coach Sharon Campbell resigned Thursday after one 
season with the Eagles. 
</P>
<P>
 Campbell, who supplemented her part-time position coaching the Eagles with 
work as a residence counselor at the university, is pursuing several other jobs 
that would combine coaching, teaching and administration. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles were 15-13, 5-5 in the Golden State Athletic Conference, under 
Campbell. 
</P>
<P>
 "This was a difficult decision for me because I like it here and this program 
has so much potential," Campbell said. "However, I know that now is the time to 
move into a full-time role." 
</P>
