<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; 2 ARRESTED IN THREATS TO WITNESS IN RAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies have arrested two Moorpark residents on suspicion of 
assaulting or intimidating a 13-year-old witness in the rape of a 12-year-old 
girl, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Claudia Mendez, 18, was taken into custody March 2 and released from County 
Jail on Tuesday.She was charged March 4 with threatening a witness, a 
misdemeanor, and is scheduled to appear March 21 for a preliminary hearing. 
</P>
<P>
 Miguel Morales, 21, was arrested Wednesday on suspicion of threatening the 
same witness. He was being held without bail in County Jail for allegedly 
violating the terms of his parole and was scheduled to be arraigned today in 
Ventura County Municipal Court. 
</P>
<P>
 The arrests came after the 13-year-old boy told deputies that Morales punched 
him in the back of the head and Mendez threatened him with a knife, according 
to Sheriff's Sgt. Marty Rouse. 
</P>
<P>
 Mendez is described as the girlfriend of Roberto Magdaleno, 22, who is accused 
of raping the 12-year-old Nov. 1 inside a recently constructed house, which was 
vacant. 
</P>
<P>
 The case is scheduled to go to trial April 25, Deputy Dist. Atty. Rebecca Day 
said. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
