<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; APPLICATIONS SOUGHT FOR ARTS COMMISSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley officials are looking for residents interested in helping run the 
city's new Cultural Arts Center. 
</P>
<P>
 A five-member Cultural Arts Center Commission, which will be selected from 
applications submitted to the City Council, will advise the council on 
operating the center.Commissioners will be appointed for three- and four-year 
terms. Appointees will also serve as the center's Board of Directors. The 
center is scheduled to open in January in a renovated church on Los Angeles 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants, who must be at least 18 and live in Simi Valley, should have a 
strong interest in the arts and be willing to help with programming and fund 
raising for the center. 
</P>
<P>
 Interested residents should call the city manager's office at 583-6701 for an 
application. The deadline for submitting applications is 5 p.m. on Friday, 
March 25. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
