<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OAK VIEW; 3 INJURED IN COLLISION THAT CLOSES HIGHWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A head-on collision injured three people, closed California 33 for an hour, 
and may have contributed to a second accident in Oak View, officials said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 With the highway closed in both directions near Creek Road after the 2:30 p.m. 
accident, firefighters worked for nearly half an hour to extricate two people 
from their mangled pickup, county fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two victims were taken to Ojai Valley Community Hospital with serious 
injuries, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 A passenger from the other truck sustained minor injuries and was also taken 
to the Ojai Valley hospital, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Their conditions were not available late Thursday, a hospital spokeswoman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The collision occurred when one truck drifted across California 33 and slammed 
into an oncoming vehicle, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortly after the crash, traffic was rerouted to Creek Road, where a 
motorcyclist sustained a broken leg in a second accident at 2:49 p.m., 
according to Ojai authorities. 
</P>
<P>
 The motorcycle accident may have been related to the increased traffic on 
Creek Road, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The names and hometowns of all the victims were withheld by the California 
Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 California 33 was reopened at 3:44 p.m. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
