<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; ST. PATRICK'S PARADE TO HONOR POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura's sixth annual St. Patrick's Day Parade will be held Saturday, 
featuring the theme, "Our Fighting Irish Heroes," and honoring all police 
officers. 
</P>
<P>
 The parade, which will begin at 10 a.m. at the San Buenaventura Mission, is 
expected to feature about 100 floats and bands from various service 
organizations and community groups. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard Police Detective Jim O'Brien, killed in a December shootout with slain 
killer Alan Winterbourne, has been named honorary grand marshal. 
</P>
<P>
 His widow Leslie and children Katie and Sean will ride in the grand marshal 
car. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-hour parade will travel through downtown Ventura and end at the 
Ventura Elks Lodge on Ash Street. The Elks Lodge will serve a meal of corned 
beef and cabbage immediately after the event. Tickets are $6 for adults and $3 
for children, and are available at the door. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
