<HEADLINE>
<P>
LYNWOOD GIRLS OVERWHELM BUENA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNEDY COSGROVE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lynwood High players and coaches said they knew it was only a matter of time 
before their pressure defense wore down Ventura Buena.  
</P>
<P>
 They were correct. 
</P>
<P>
 Midway through the third quarter of Thursday night's Southern Regional 
Division I girls' basketball semifinal at Lynwood, Buena led by one point. 
</P>
<P>
 But Lynwood outscored the Bulldogs by 22 points the rest of the way to win, 
59-38, and advance to the regional final on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 "We knew Buena was going to come out and play us tough for a couple of 
quarters," said Timicha Kirby, who led Lynwood with 25 points. "But we knew our 
defense would pull us through." 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second consecutive year that the Knights (31-1) defeated the 
Bulldogs (25-3) in the state tournament. Last season, Lynwood beat Buena in the 
regional final by 11 points and went on to win the state championship. 
</P>
<P>
 "In terms of natural athletic ability, they have much more than us," Buena 
Coach Joe Vaughan said. "They should be good." KENNEDY COSGROVE 
</P>
