<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; MATER DEI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Schea Cotton scored 36 points to lead Santa Ana Mater Dei to an 84-68 victory 
over Fresno Bullard Thursday night at Ocean View High in the Division I 
semifinals of the CIF Southern Regional tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Cotton, a 6-foot-5 freshman, made 13 of 19 shots, including six dunks for the 
Monarchs (33-0). He had 18 in the first half, which ended in a 33-33 tie. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei scored 51 points in the second half and put the game away with a 
15-4 run to start the fourth quarter. Cotton scored eight of those points. 
</P>
<P>
 Shannon Taylor scored 15 points for Bullard (25-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Crenshaw 66, Long Beach Poly 59 -- The Cougars used a pressure defense to 
defeat Poly in a Division I semifinal at Cal State Dominguez Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Crenshaw will play Mater Dei Saturday at 7:30 p.m. at the Anaheim Arena in the 
Southern Regional final. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cougars (27-2) forced 16 turnovers in the first half, including 10 in the 
first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Reggie McFerren, a 6-foot-6 guard, scored 10 of his 18 points in the first 
quarter as the Cougars took an 18-8 lead and were never threatened. Tremaine 
Fowlkes scored 25 points to lead Crenshaw. Damion Dawson led Poly (26-6) with 
18 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Bakersfield East 70, Riverside North 61 -- UCLA-bound J.R. Henderson scored 28 
points to lead Bakersfield East (27-4) in a Division II victory over North 
(29-2) at Bakersfield East. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove Pacifica 65, San Diego St. Augustine 62 -- Pacifica rallied from 
a 20-point second-half deficit and guard Ryan Teague scored four points in the 
final 40 seconds to break a 61-61 tie before 3,000 in a Division III game at 
Cypress College. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Vlasic had 27 points, including five three-pointers, for Pacifica 
(29-1). Jelani McCoy had 19 points, 18 rebounds and five blocked shots for St. 
Augustine (25-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Verbum Dei 103, Santa Fe Springs St. Paul 76 -- Jamaal Cobbs scored 24 points 
and Andre Miller added 19 points and six steals to lead Verbum Dei (26-2) to a 
Division IV victory over St. Paul (17-13) at Compton College. GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Woodbridge 84, San Bernardino 63 -- Guard Jamie Oenning scored 21 
points to lead Woodbridge (31-0) past San Bernardino (26-7) in a Division II 
game at Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 63, Santee Santana 51 -- Gina Heads scored 16 points and 
Genevieve Evarts had 14 to lead Newport Harbor (24-7) over Santana (26-4) in a 
Division III game at Santana. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ynez 65, Cerritos Valley Christian 60 -- Kristi Rohr scored 25 points 
and grabbed 13 rebounds to lead Santa Ynez (26-5) to a Division IV victory at 
Valley Christian (27-3). 
</P>
<P>
 El Cajon Christian 74, San Luis Obispo Mission Prep 39 -- Jenny Wenning scored 
22 points to lead El Cajon Christian (27-4) to a Division V victory over 
Mission Prep (19-7) at Christian High. 
