<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANITA; SKYLAUNCH RALLIES IN STRETCH TO BEAT NANCYS FRENCH FRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Skylaunch, ridden by Gary Stevens, lagged back until the stretch to win the 
$40,000 feature by 1 1/4 lengths Thursday at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 Nancys French Fry, the favorite under Fernando Valenzuela, finished second, 2 
1/4 lengths in front of Private Premier in a field of seven in the allowance 
race for 4-year-olds and up, all carrying 118 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Skylaunch, a 6-year-old Kentucky-bred gelding, covered a mile over a fast 
track in 1:35 4-5 and paid $5.60, $2.80 and $2.40 as the second choice. He 
earned $22,000 for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Nancys French Fry returned $2.80 and $2.20 and Private Premier, with Eddie 
Delahoussaye aboard, showed at $2.60. 
</P>
<P>
 Nancys French Fry made her move on the final turn and had the advantage at the 
furlong marker but could not maintain the pace. Private Premier had the lead by 
a head at the three-quarter mark. 
</P>
<P>
 Stevens won his third race in the ninth aboard longshot Wild Lightning, paying 
$39.20 for the win. He won the third race aboard Gavel Gate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
