<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXPLOSIVE LYNWOOD WEARS DOWN BUENA; DIVISION I GIRLS: KNIGHTS RALLY IN SECOND 
HALF WITH PRESSURE DEFENSE TO WIN GOING AWAY, 59-38. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNEDY COSGROVE, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lynwood High players and coaches said they knew it was only a matter of time 
before their pressure defense wore down the Buena girls' basketball team. 
</P>
<P>
 They were correct. 
</P>
<P>
 Midway through the third quarter of Thursday's State Southern Regional 
semifinal, Buena led by a point. 
</P>
<P>
 But Lynwood outscored the Bulldogs by 22 the rest of the way to win, 59-38, 
and advance to the regional final on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 "We knew Buena was going to come out and play us tough for a couple of 
quarters," said Knight forward Timicha Kirby, who scored a game-high 25 points. 
"But we knew our defense would pull us through." 
</P>
<P>
 Said Buena Coach Joe Vaughan: "In terms of natural athletic ability, they have 
much more than us." 
</P>
<P>
 It marked the second consecutive year that the Knights (31-1) defeated the 
Bulldogs (25-3) in the state tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Last season, Lynwood beat them in the regional final by 11 points and went on 
to win the state championship. 
</P>
<P>
 "Right at the end of the third quarter was a turning point," Vaughan said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Then I thought we got a little careless with the ball. You have to keep them 
in a half-court game." 
</P>
<P>
 In the first half, that's exactly what Buena did. The Bulldogs' zone defense 
and inside strength caused problems for Lynwood, as Buena center Michelle 
Giordano drew foul after foul near the basket. 
</P>
<P>
 Giordano, a 6-0 senior who has enjoyed a brilliant career at Buena and has 
signed with Arizona, scored 10 first-half points, all on free throws. But she 
scored only five in the second half before fouling out. 
</P>
<P>
 "She had a great game, and I wish her all the best at Arizona," Kirby said of 
Giordano. "But it's team defense that wins championships and that's what we 
thrive on here at Lynwood." 
</P>
</TEXT>
