<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES; CAZETT STEPS DOWN AS GIRLS' BASKETBALL COACH AT FOOTHILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dean Cazett has resigned as Foothill High girls' basketball coach because of 
time constraints. 
</P>
<P>
 Cazett coached the Knights for two years.They were 6-17 this season after 
going 1-20 in 1992-93. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda's Southern California Division III girls' championship game 
Saturday will be broadcast on KMNY 1600 AM. 
</P>
<P>
 Brea will play Newport Harbor at 9:30 a.m. at Anaheim Arena. The broadcast 
will begin at 10 a.m. on a 30-minute tape delay. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Bobby Bruch, who led Marina to its second consecutive Division I girls' soccer 
title, will coach the North team in the Orange County all-star game March 23 at 
Chapman University. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei's Michelle Myers will coach the South team. The game is sponsored by 
the county's girls' soccer coaches association and will feature seniors from 
teams with a coach who is a member of the organization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
