<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP TRACK ROUNDUP; BYRD BREAKS FOUNTAIN VALLEY HIGH JUMP RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fountain Valley's Matt Byrd broke a 15-year-old school record in the high 
jump, clearing 6 feet 5 3/4 in a 94-34 victory over Westminster in a Sunset 
League boys' track and field meet Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Rick Bays jumped 6-5 for Fountain Valley in 1979. 
</P>
<P>
 Jamal Hills won the 100 in 11.7 seconds and the 200 in 23.7 for Fountain 
Valley (1-0 in league). 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sunset League boys' track: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 68, Huntington Beach 67 -- Junior Jason Bader, who finished fourth at 
the Sunkist Indoor meet last month, won the discus with a throw of 178 feet 2 
inches for Edison (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 75, Ocean View 61 -- Jeremy Womack won the 400 meters (51.8) and 300 
hurdles (41.3) and David Shaw won the long jump (20-3 1/2) and the triple jump 
(43-4 1/2) for Ocean View (1-1, 0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Servite 72, Santa Ana 64 -- Carlos Rodriguez won the 100 in 11.5 and the 200 
in 24.4 for Santa Ana (0-1, 0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In Garden Grove League boys' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove 88, Rancho Alamitos 39 -- Mike Balderas won the 880 in 2:08 and 
the mile in 4:59 to lead visiting Garden Grove (2-0, 2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Los Amigos 90, Kennedy 38 -- Sophomore Luis Renteria won the 1,600 (5:09.3) 
and the 3,200 (11:22) for Los Amigos (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In Sea View League boys' track: 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 81, University 46 -- Wade Tiff won the shotput in 60-10 for 
Newport Harbor (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 78, Saddleback 58 -- Gary Young won the 100 and 200 for Woodbridge 
(2-0, 1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 64, Buena Park 48, Magnolia 47 -- Greg Cleave won the 100 yards (10.4) 
and the 220 (22.9) and Ali Mohammad won the 440 (54.5) and the two mile (10:36) 
for Cypress (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 98, Aliso Niguel 39 -- Brett Daeley won the 100 in 11.3, the 100 
hurdles in 17.5, the long jump at 20 feet and anchored the winning 400-relay 
team for El Modena (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 78, Valencia 68, Troy 18 -- Katella (1-0) won seven of 10 events, 
including both relays. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 74, Sunny Hills 58 -- Jaime Martinez won the 1,600 and 3,200 and Jeff 
Williams won the 100 meter and 300 hurdles for Orange (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 85, Laguna Hills 32 -- Victor Ruble won the 100 meters in 11.5 
seconds and the 200 meter in 24.2 for San Clemente (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna 81, Loara 46 -- Mike Flores won the 100 (11.2) and 200 (23.3) and 
Aaron Woosley also was a double winner, taking the high jump and triple jump 
for Savanna (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In Garden Grove League girls' track: 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove 88, Rancho Alamitos 37 -- Erin Nelson won three events to lead 
Garden Grove (2-0, 2-0). She won the 440 in 68.8, the 880 in 2:43.9, and the 
330 hurdles in 52.6. Nicole Murray won the 100 yards (11.8) and 220 (29.4). 
</P>
<P>
 Los Amigos 87, Kennedy 42 -- Carmela Zavala won the 800 and the 1,600 for Los 
Amigos (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In Sea View League girls' track: 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 88, University 38 -- The Sailors won every event in their 
league opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 74, Saddleback 48 -- Woodbridge (1-0, 1-0) won all but four events. 
Wilson Duvall led the Warriors with victories in the 100 (12.7) and 200 (26.4). 
Gabbey Martinez won the 800, 1,600 and the 3,200 for Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 In Sunset League girls' track: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 90, Huntington Beach 37 -- Kerry O'Bric and Marie Philman combined to 
win seven events for Edison (2-0, 1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 98, Westminster 29 -- Becca Armour won the 1,600 and 3,200 in 
5:41.2 and 12:14 for Fountain Valley (1-0). Marlene Lang won the 200 in 27.5 
and the 300 hurdles in 47.0. Lisa Tamasui of Westminster won the shotput and 
the discus with throws of 35-2 and 106-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 64, Ocean View 63 -- Sonya Bryant won the shotput and discus for 
visiting Marina (2-0, 1-0). Donna Garcia won the 200 (27.5) and 400 (1:02.1), 
and was part of Ocean View's winning 400 relay and 1,600 relay teams. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosary 76, Santa Ana 46 -- Lizzie Shilling won the 200 in 29.4 and the 300 
hurdles in 54.3 for Rosary (1-0). Linnea Housewright won the high jump at 5-0. 
Jackie Rodriguez won the 1,600 in 6:03.0 and the 3,200 in 12:58.3 for Santa Ana 
(0-1, 0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' track: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 90, Villa Park 37 -- Meghan Mayes won the 800 and 1,600 
races for Capistrano Valley. Villa Park's Meghan Reppe won the 100 and 200. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 68, Buena Park 66, Magnolia 25 -- Carrie Garritson won the mile 
(5:39.8) and the two mile (13:19) for Buena Park (2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 84, Aliso Niguel 41 -- Kaylee Whitfield won the 400 in 1:03.4, the 
800 in 2:35.6 and the 300 hurdles in 51.3 for El Modena (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 74, Sonora 42, Brea-Olinda 30 -- Kelly Daucher won the 1,600 (5:34.8) 
and the 3,200 (12:27) for Brea-Olinda (2-2). Marsha Conrad won the shotput 
(33-6 3/4) and discus (105-10 1/2) for the Wildcats. 
</P>
<P>
 Loara 68, Savanna 59 -- Pearl Mercer won the 100 and 200 meters and Christina 
Mantas won the triple jump (31-5) and the discus (96-2) for Loara (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Los Amigos 85, Kennedy 42 -- Summer McCloskey won the 200 in 29.5, the long 
jump in 14-9 and the triple jump in 31-5 1/2 for Kennedy (0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 66, Sunny Hills 58 -- Delphia Moore won the 200 and 300 hurdles and ran 
a leg on Orange's winning 400 relay team. 
</P>
