<HEADLINE>
<P>
BREA-OLINDA, IRVINE INVITATIONALS SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The high school track season breaks into full stride this weekend when many of 
Orange County's top programs compete in invitationals Saturday at Brea-Olinda 
and Irvine high schools. 
</P>
<P>
 The Brea-Olinda Invitational, which has nearly tripled in size from last year, 
features 20 squads from Southern California -- 14 of which are from the 
county.Field events begin at 8 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Two of the county's top boys' teams -- Foothill and Cypress -- will compete at 
Brea. Seniors Ethan Taub (Foothill) and Jimmy Hutsell (Cypress) will renew 
their duel in the 400 meters. Taub edged Hutsell by one-tenth of a second in 
the 500-yard run at last month's Sunkist Indoor Invitational at the Sports 
Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park senior Carrie Garritson, the county's cross-country champion, and 
Corona del Mar senior Jason Boyce, the county leader in the long jump and 
100-meter sprint, also are expected to compete at Brea. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine Invitational, which begins at 8:30 a.m., will feature two boys' 
teams -- Woodbridge and Esperanza -- expected to battle for the county title in 
April. On the girls' side, Laguna Hills and El Toro will compete along with a 
strong returning squad from Esperanza. MATT FARMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
