<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CYPRESS EDGES GOLDEN WEST IN BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 David Trentine doubled in Mario Opipari in the bottom of the eighth inning to 
lead Cypress to a 3-2 victory over Golden West in an Orange Empire Conference 
baseball game Thursday at Cypress College. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Hodges had two doubles and scored the tying run in the bottom of the 
seventh for the Chargers. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore pitcher Aaron France won his sixth game of the season as Cypress 
pushed its record to 16-4, 4-1 in conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West dropped to 7-9 and 1-4 in conference. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire conference baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 16, Orange Coast 5 -- Tim Walker, Chad Smith and Steve Escobar 
homered for Fullerton. Walker's home run was part of Fullerton's six-run second 
inning. Smith and Escobar hit theirs back-to-back in a four-run fourth. Three 
Pirate errors in the sixth inning led to six more runs for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Erickson Dumaual went three for four with two doubles for Fullerton. Orange 
Coast's Richard Ernst had a single, double and triple and scored twice. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 5, Rancho Santiago 3 -- Brian Downs and Andy Rojo each homered for 
visiting Riverside (15-2, 5-0). Darren Troilo had two hits and Mike Bellovich 
had a double and two RBIs for Rancho Santiago (15-4, 3-2). 
</P>
