<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; THE MASTER'S POUNDS SCC PITCHING, 15-4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Master's pounded Southern California College pitching for 15 hits and took 
advantage of seven errors to win, 15-4, in a nonconference baseball game 
Thursday in Newhall. 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's (6-10-2) scored four runs in the first, two in the third and 
three in the fourth to take a 9-2 lead against starter Augie Pena (1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Smith had four hits, including two doubles, and drove in four runs, and 
Mark Vail added three hits and four RBIs for The Master's. 
</P>
<P>
 Ila Borders, making her first relief appearance, entered in the eighth inning 
trailing 11-4. She walked the leadoff batter, and three ground-ball errors and 
a single gave The Master's four unearned runs. SCC is 6-12. 
</P>
<P>
 In another nonconference baseball game: 
</P>
<P>
 UC San Diego 4, Concordia 1 -- Concordia (5-11) fell behind 3-0 after three 
innings and was held hitless 7 1/3 innings. The Eagles managed only two hits. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference men's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Point Loma Nazarene 9, Southern California College 0 -- SCC's Ross Andel won 
his first set against Victor Vernis, 6-4, but dropped the next two, 6-1, 6-4. 
</P>
