<P>
 Rostenkowski case -- A story that appeared Tuesday in The Times said that 
prosecutors conducting a grand jury investigation into the financial affairs of 
Rep. Dan Rostenkowski (D-Ill.) had remained on the case despite the change from 
a Republican to a Democratic Administration.The top attorney, U.S. Atty. Jay 
Stephens, was replaced by U.S. Atty. Eric H. Holder Jr. after President Clinton 
took office. However, the career prosecutors conducting the day-to-day 
investigation remain the same. 
